Link to instructions:
https://medium.com/@dheerubhadoria/capturing-images-from-camera-in-android-with-jetpack-compose-a-step-by-step-guide-64cd7f52e5de
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Edit "build.gradle (Module :app)":
    add -> buildConfig = true
    add -> Coil Dependency
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Make path_provider.xml File:
    make File in -> res > xml > path_provider.xml
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Edit "AndroidManifest.xml":
    add -> user-feature for Camera
    add -> user-permission for Camera

    add -> <provider></provider> for File Creation in <application></application>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Add Icon to res > drawable:
    add -> camera.png ( <a href="https://www.flaticon.com/free-icons/camera">Icons by Freepik@Flaticon</a> )
    add -> scan.png ( <a href="https://www.flaticon.com/free-icons/scan">Icons by Freepik@Flaticon</a> )
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Edit "build.gradle (Module :app)":
    add -> System-Bar Customization Dependency

